# .dockerignore — files excluded from the Docker build context
#
# The build context is everything sent to the Docker daemon when you run
# `docker compose up --build`. Smaller context = faster builds.
#
# These files are not needed inside the container:

# Git history — large, unnecessary at runtime
.git
.gitignore

# Local environment files — secrets must come from docker-compose.yml environment vars,
# never baked into the image (images can be shared or pushed to registries)
.env
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*

# Other stage directories — we only need stage-10 source.
# The Dockerfile builds ./stage-10-deployment/ specifically.
# Including other stages would make the context huge and rebuild unnecessarily.
stage-01-basics/
stage-02-routing/
stage-03-middleware/
stage-04-database/
stage-05-auth/
stage-06-validation/
stage-07-config/
stage-08-logging/
stage-09-testing/

# Markdown files — documentation not needed at runtime
*.md

# Test files — not needed in production image
**/*_test.go
**/testhelpers/
